#slide[
  = JIT Compilation <jit-compilation>

  Just-In-Time (JIT) compilation happens while the program is running, rather than before.

  - *Performance*: Combines the flexibility of interpretation with the speed of compiled code.
  - *Optimization*: Can optimize code based on runtime data.
  - *Use cases*: Browsers (V8), JVM, and interactive REPLs.
]
